                <h1>Understanding Asthma: Symptoms, Triggers, and Management</h1>
                <p>Asthma is a chronic respiratory condition characterized by inflamed airways, making breathing difficult. Common symptoms include wheezing, coughing, chest tightness, and shortness of breath. It can be triggered by allergens, pollution, or stress. Proper management with medications and lifestyle adjustments is crucial for improving quality of life.</p>
